                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d860">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-09-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Eddy transmits the reply of the minister for foreign affairs in regard to
                    the exchange of the Russian and Japanese prisoners of war which states that the
                    Imperial Government snares entirely the point of view of the Japanese Government
                    as to accelerating as much as possible the preparations of the exchange of the
                    prisoners, and accepts in principle the proposition for the return of the
                    Japanese prisoners on the western frontier of the Empire and for receiving the
                    prisoners of war and other Russians detained in Japan at the ports of Nagasaki,
                    Kobe, and Yokohama as soon as the preliminary arrangements are completed. The
                    Russian Government will immediately communicate with the Japanese Government
                    through the usual diplomatic channels.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
